winter dreams ❄️ 
.
LOTS of work went into setting this shoot up. 😅
Firstly, designer @olena_krevenets spent days cutting out the angel backdrop by hand. 
Then while our amazing model @witchplease666 was getting her makeup expertly done by @glowwithvicksmua , we set up the whole scene in her garage with all sorts of accent and back lighting, Christmas lights, trees, fabrics etc. 
The dreamy effect around the edges in the pictures isn't a filter or editing but was created in camera using some bubble plastic wrap to partially block the lens. Then we hung some little lights in the foreground to get some lovely bokeh 😍
.

Diving into Christmas like... SuitandTieGuy!

Well we didn't have a chance to do a full photoshoot with this crazy cold snap we're having, but we did get out to play in the snow for a little bit. It was -10 C (14°F) when we did this 🥶😆 Needless to say my poor brother Dave was a bit chilly.

social_posts.post_text:
Behind the scenes from yesterday's Christmas Eve post! 🎅✌️ 
I was so impressed with how our non-professional stuntman @suitandtieguy_ pulled off the dive at the end. There was a lot to think about between lighting the firework, pulling pin on the the smokebomb, then running and diving at the right time while throwing everything in the air and sliding into the exact place I asked him to land in 😂 Not to mention it was frighteningly cold out and he had already taken a few snowballs to the face 😆🥶 We only had one take and he nailed it! 🙌🙌
.
Hope you're all having a wonderful holiday season 🫶 And once again Merry Christmas!
.
#christmasfun #olddudesdoingstupidshit #wintersports #snowdiving #suitandtieguy #christmasspirit

Night of the Living Dead Girl 🧟‍♀️🔥
.
Behind the scenes from my recent collaboration with killer model @itstinalouise , special FX makeup artist extraordinaire @mikemakesmonsters , and amazing mua @izfx.mua 🙌
.
Mike made prosthetic coverings that moulded over parts of Tina's body that made it look like wounds, and then they spent many hours to apply it and blend it in with makeup. The gashes and slashes were so realistic it gave me shivers 😱 
There's no nudity here, she's covered up in all the right places with the prosthetic material 😉
.
Big thanks to @robert.lund.313 for the set location 🙌👊

Back to the Future 2023 - Have you seen these $@%&! gas prices?! 
.
So much fun recreating this Back to the Future movie poster with @bcdelorean .
All effects were created in camera. The final result is two shots blended together, the first shot with fog and lighting trying to match the poster, and a second long exposure shot with fire. I used a tripod and kept my camera in the same position for both shots which made for an easy blend using Photoshop. 
.
Huge thanks to @shitspackledmuppetfart and @ryandoell31 for all the amazing behind the scenes help with fog, lighting, etc. 🙌🙌
.
Stay tuned for more from this shoot with McFly and his amazing DeLorean Time Machine coming soon! 
.

Graveyard Shift 🪦 ... Swipe and please let me know your favourites plus check out the raw BTS footage with @katydecobray as Van Helsing! 
No added digital effects. Each shot is a single exposure #nophotoshop 
.
I've had a few comments in the past that it would be a lot easier to just use photoshop to make backgrounds and add effects instead of going out in the freezing rain for a couple of hours, getting myself and my gear soaked, and packing around a wagon full of equipment, lights, special effects stuff, etc in order to get the shots. 
Number one, I suck at photoshop 😂 ...but really for myself I enjoy the challenge of capturing things on camera and creating scenes using the location, lighting, and special fx like smoke, fog, and fire to hopefully make some magic happen for real. 
Plus it's a lot of fun meeting so many awesome artists and creatives and making some great friends along the way. 
 .
BTS vid clips/fog: @supermediocrephotography 
.
.

Ocean Garden... What's your favourite shot?
.
Such fun making magic with this amazing team of creatives. 
Designer @olena_krevenets came up with the concept of using vivid neon colours on a dark background and set up the entire scene in her small garage. 
Then makeup artist @iriee.artistry spent hours applying full body UV sensitive makeup while hairstylist @oksi_model styled the hair interwoven with neon fabrics. 
And of course model @cayetanamolla was fabulous as always. 🙌
.
The original concept was not actually meant to look like it was underwater but to me a lot of the pictures look like they are in an aquarium. What do you think? 😃
.

Introducing the revolutionary Molus x100 COB video/photography light from @zhiyun_tech ...Definitely my new favourite light! 
This cool vintage style bi-colour COB (high powered LED) light packs professional power in a lightweight pocket sized package.
Super important to me is being able to use the 100w battery power as I'm usually shooting outdoors or don't want to have power cords everywhere. The light can also be powered using the DC power adapter, or 100W PD fast charge.
.
Some of you might ask… Dave, why aren't you just using a flash to light the model? Why continuous lighting? 
I like using continuous lighting because I can see in real time what the lighting is looking like, rather than the trial and error of using a flash. The problem with most portable LED lights is that they are just not bright enough in a lot of challenging situations. During this set I was shooting with the sun directly behind the model and a very bright main light is needed to overcome the brightness of the sun. This light performed amazingly well. 👍
.
Click the link in my bio and check it out if you want to be one of the first to have one of these wicked new lights from ZHIYUN !
.

Cry for Ukraine 2 - Our photo project is not just a collection of what we hope are meaningful images, but a powerful statement about the devastating impact of the Russian invasion on the Ukrainian people. Each photograph is a testament to the pain, grief, and resilience of a nation under attack, and the traditional symbols and imagery we’ve used serve to amplify the raw emotion of the experience. We’ve chosen to focus on the human cost of the war, the toll it takes on individuals and families, in the hope that it will inspire empathy and understanding among those who may have previously been skeptical or uninformed about the situation. Our goal is to create a narrative that cannot be ignored, one that demands attention and action from anyone who sees it. By bearing witness to the suffering of the Ukrainian people, we hope to spark a deeper conversation and a greater sense of urgency about the need for peace and justice.
.
